{"word":"φρούριον","slug":"φρούριον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φρούριον</b></el> <el>(φρούριον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:φρουρός'><el>φρουρός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>a watch-post, garrisoned fort, citadel</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>the guard, garrison</i>, of a place, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}